{{Multiple issues| {{refimprove|date=July 2008}} {{disputed|date=July 2008}} {{Orphan|date=November 2013}} }} {{Infobox Magazine | title = Hispanic Enterprise | image_file = Hispanic Enterprise Magazine Cover.png | image_size = 200px | image_caption = ''Hispanic Enterprise Magazine'', June–July 2007 Issue | editor = [[Carlos Alfaro]] | frequency = Monthly | circulation = ~170,000 | category = [[:Category:American business magazines|Business Magazines]] | publisher = [[Televisa Publishing]], a [[Televisa]] company. | founded = 2002 | firstdate = | finaldate = July 2008 | country = United States | based = [[Miami, Florida]] | language = [[English language|English]] | website = [http://www.hispanicenterprisemagazine.net www.hispanicenterprisemagazine.com] }}
'''''Hispanic Enterprise Magazine''''', formerly '''''Hispanic Trends Magazine''''', was a joint project of Editorial Televisa<ref name=bwir>{{cite news|title=PODER Magazine Launches Miami Edition|url=http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20071001005465/en/PODER-Magazine-Launches-Miami-Edition|accessdate=18 November 2015|work=BusinessWire|date=1 October 2007}}</ref> and the United States Hispanic Chamber of Commerce. Its headquarters was in Miami, Florida.<ref name=bwir/> The publication is a source of news, features and information for every Hispanic entrepreneur and anyone affiliated with the Hispanic marketplace. In 2006, ''Hispanic Enterprise'' successfully launched its digital version.
Published in English, ''Hispanic Enterprise'' aimed at the business community of Hispanic entrepreneurs. It was primarily distributed to members of the United States Hispanic Chamber of Commerce, which at last count in 2005, numbered approximately 2 million in the United States, generating almost $300 billion in annual gross receipt.
In July 2008, the magazine was combined with ''[[PODER Magazine]]''<ref>[http://www.marketingymedios.com/marketingymedios/noticias/article_display.jsp?vnu_content_id=1003830382 Televisa Combines 'Poder' and 'Hispanic Enterprise']</ref> and started circulating under the name ''PODER Enterprise''.<ref>{{cite news|title=The Newly Titled Poder Enterprise Grows Its Circulation|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/apps/news?pid=conewsstory&tkr=CHILES:CI&sid=a0tuDmhrAf7U|accessdate=18 November 2015|work=Bloomberg|date=31 July 2008|location=Miami, Florida}}</ref>
