{{NZ parlbox footer}}
He served on numerous boards and committees: the [[Buller District|Buller County Council]] (1885–89), [[Westport, New Zealand|Westport]] Harbour Board (Chairman 1890), and was [[Mayor]] of Westport between 1898 and 1900.{{sfn|Scholefield|1940|p=171}}

Colvin stood in the {{NZ electorate link|Buller}} electorate in the {{NZ election link|1896}} but was defeated by [[Patrick O'Regan]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Buller Electoral District |url= http://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/cgi-bin/paperspast?a=d&cl=search&d=IT18961202.2.14.1 |accessdate=13 January 2014 |newspaper=Inangahua Times |date=2 December 1896 |volume=XXI |issue=1092 |page=3}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Nelson |url= http://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/cgi-bin/paperspast?a=d&cl=search&d=AS18961223.2.28.12 |accessdate=13 January 2014 |newspaper=[[Auckland Star]] |date=23 December 1896 |volume=XXVII |issue=305 |page=6}}</ref> He defeated O'Regan in [[New Zealand general election, 1899|1899]] as a supporter of [[Richard Seddon]],{{sfn|Scholefield|1940|p=171}} and represented the Buller electorate in the [[New Zealand House of Representatives|House of Representatives]] for twenty years until his death in 1919. At the {{NZ election link|1899}}, Colvin stood as an [[Independent Liberal]] rather than an official Liberal candidate.{{sfn|Wilson|1985|p=190}}

Colvin served as the [[Chairman of Committees (New Zealand House of Representatives)|Chairman of Committees]] from 1910 to 1911.{{sfn|Wilson|1985|p=252}} In the house, he had the nickname 'uncle Colvin', given to him by [[Thomas Wilford]] in 1899 when they both entered Parliament.<ref name="Press obit" /> He was [[Minister (government)|Minister]] of [[Mining|Mines]] in 1912 in the Mackenzie cabinet.{{sfn|Wood |1996 |p=88}}

Colvin was killed at 10 pm on 29 October 1919 by a tram as he left Parliament House in 1919.{{sfn|Matthews|1999|p=203}} Parliament was still sitting, and the news reached the debating chamber within 15 minutes, which resulted in the immediate adjournment of proceedings.<ref name="Press obit" />

